DevSecOps (Development + Security + Operations) means embedding security into every stage of the DevOps pipeline, instead of treating it as a final checkpoint.

Instead of: Build → Test → Deploy → then check security ❌

DevSecOps does: Plan → Code → Build → Test → Release → Deploy → Monitor

with security at every step ✅

Key idea:

“Shift Left Security” → catch vulnerabilities early (during coding/build stage)

Automate security checks inside CI/CD pipelines

Example in real pipeline:

Developer commits code -→

Pipeline runs:
  Static code scan (SonarQube)
  Dependency scan (Mend)
  Container scan (Trivy)
  Dynamic scan (OWASP ZAP)

Only if everything passes → deploy
